'You dishonestly failed to notify changes in your circumstances. You were given ample opportunity to come clean but you failed to do that.

'You knew exactly what you were doing.'

Hollingworth, who struggled to stand up in court and had to use the wall for support, made no reaction as he was given a 16 week sentence, suspended for two years.

He was also fitted with an electronic tag and given a six month curfew from the hours of 7pm to 7am.

