Hollingworth was ordered to pay £200 pounds in court costs and an £80 victim surcharge, before limping out of court.

Vernon Sanderson, DWP fraud manager in the North West, said: 'It is our duty to ensure that benefit payments go to those who really need them and we are committed to cracking down on those who play the system.

'Our welfare reforms are vital to close the gaps that cheats take advantage of.

